1. Eliminate unnecessary re-renders
    = Use React.memo for list items
    = Without this, every render recreates functions → all items re-render.

2. Optimize expensive computation
    = Memoize filtered list
    = Filtering on every render = O(n) cost repeatedly.

3. Virtualize large lists (critical for >100 items)
    = react-window
    = react-virtualized
    = Only visible items render → massive performance gain.
    
    syntax = import { FixedSizeList as List } from "react-window";) 

4. Debounce search input
    = Use lodash.debounce
    = Prevents filtering on every keystroke → reduces unnecessary computations.

5. Lazy load components
    = React.lazy + Suspense
    = Reduces initial bundle size.

6. Avoid unnecessary state
    = Keep state minimal
    = Derived state → compute, don’t store.

7. Optimize API calls
    = Cache results (e.g., with React Query)
    = Avoid duplicate fetches
    = Use pagination / infinite scroll

8. Key correctness

9. Image optimization
    = Use smaller thumbnails
    = Lazy load


10. Priority order (do this first)
    = Virtualization
    = Memoization (memo, useMemo, useCallback)
    = Debouncing
    = API optimization
    = Lazy loading